## Tasks in priority order

### Task A — Dashboard: render module tiles
Read `access_tree.modules[]` from localStorage. Render one tile per module.
Each tile shows:
- `module_name` (e.g., "RMS")
- `description` (e.g., "Resource Management System")
- Click handler: open chat for that module.

DO NOT render collections or agents on the dashboard. The user does not pick a collection or persona — backend infers both from the user's message.

If `access_tree.modules` is empty, show a message: "You don't have access to any modules. Contact your administrator."

### Task B — Chat window: open from a module tile
When the user clicks a module tile, open a chat interface. The chat:
- Has a title showing the module name (e.g., "RMS Chat").
- Has a message input area.
- Has a message display area (empty at first).
- Has no collection selector. No persona selector. No agent dropdown. These have all been removed.

For now, show an empty chat or a simple greeting like "Hi! What can I help you with?"

### Task C — Send a chat message
On submit, POST to `/api/v1/chat/stream` with body:
```json
{
  "module_name": "RMS",
  "message": "<user's message text>",
  "chat_history": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "previous user msg"},
    {"role": "assistant", "content": "previous AI msg"}
  ],
  "thread_id": "<optional uuid from previous response, omit on first message>"
}